  "about": {
    "label": "About",
    "title": "The Spirit of Hawaiian Waters",
    "p1": "Where the black lava meets the turquoise sea, Honl's Beach has long been a gathering place for riders who understand the ocean's ancient rhythms. Here, the shore break creates perfect conditions for the art of bodyboarding—a tradition born in these very waters.",
    "p2": "This competition honors the spirit of Hawaiian watermanship, welcoming riders of all ages and abilities to test their skills against the waves of the Kona coast."
  },
